        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2 class="steps" style="color:#5bc0de">Step 1 - Adding Classes</h2>
          <p class="indent">
            Before joining any group, you need to find your classes first!<br>Add your classes by clicking "Add another class" and the drop down menu
            will appear. As soon as you click one of the classes from the list, it will automatically add that class for you. 
          </p>

          <img class="col-mid-12 img-responsive" align="center" src="/images/help_1.JPG" style="padding:10px;">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4" id="mypagebody">
          <h2 class="steps" style="color:#5bc0de">Step 2 - View Groups</h2>
          <p class="indent">
            This is a list of your saved classes on your left. If you click a specific class, it will 
            direct you to the class page.<br>Here, you can see the full list of groups associated with each class. If you are not in that group, you would not see any relevant information until you join. 
          </p>
          <img class="col-mid-12 img-responsive" src="/images/help_2.JPG" align="center" style="padding:10px;">
       </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2 class="steps" style="color:#5bc0de">Step 3 - Meeting With Your Group</h2>
          <p class="indent">
             After choosing class, we will show the the groups already formed by other Groupers.
             There are two different lists for the group: one type is IN-PERSON and the other
             is ONLINE.<br><br>If you click a group from IN-PERSON, it will show you the time, place, and number of people for the group meetings. If you choose ONLINE, you will be given access to the website the group is being held.
          </p>
          <p class="indent">
            If you do not like groups already formed, you can always create one yourself
            by clicking CREATE GROUP button on the side!
          </p>
          <img class="col-mid-12 img-responsive" src="/images/help_3.JPG" align="center" style="padding:10px;">
        </div>
